bullets: Moderate p3ht_content with a mid-range total dopant (d2_content + d6_content + d8_content) tends to maximize conductivity
Increasing d2_content (shorter/stronger dopant) at fixed p3ht_content typically raises conductivity
keep d8_content low while letting d2_content dominate for peak conductivity.
Too high p3ht_content with very low combined (d2_content + d6_content + d8_content) under-dopes the film; raise d2_content first before increasing d6_content to unlock conductivity.
When p3ht_content is low (polymer-poor), reduce d8_content and lean on d2_content to avoid over-swelling and preserve π–π stacking pathways.
Conductivity often shows a peak vs total dopant; if (d2_content + d6_content + d8_content) is already high, decrease d8_content first, then d6_content, while keeping d2_content as the primary dopant.
